WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:55.134 --> 00:00:57.010
Whoever gets to the temple first win!

3
00:00:57.011 --> 00:00:58.010
What?

4
00:00:58.011 --> 00:00:59.622
Aang. no fair!

5
00:01:01.357 --> 00:01:02.406
Let's get him!

6
00:01:02.431 --> 00:01:03.431
Hurry up!

7
00:01:12.454 --> 00:01:13.950
- Hi. Nima.
- Good morning. Aang.

8
00:01:13.975 --> 00:01:15.557
- Hei. mipmip.
- Oh. hello. Aang.

9
00:01:22.110 --> 00:01:24.109
Oh. perfect timing.

10
00:01:24.661 --> 00:01:26.030
I don't mind giving me a lift.

11
00:01:26.031 --> 00:01:28.030
Gyatso. this isn't the best time.

12
00:01:28.105 --> 00:01:30.030
I'm getting old. you know.

13
00:01:30.031 --> 00:01:32.312
My body doesn't move like it used to.

14
00:01:32.337 --> 00:01:34.571
I'm kind of in the middle of something.

15
00:01:34.711 --> 00:01:35.972
You are so heavy.

16
00:01:35.997 --> 00:01:37.454
Heavy? Me?

17
00:01:37.479 --> 00:01:39.174
I eat nothing but vegetables.

18
00:01:39.199 --> 00:01:41.257
Pie is not a vegetable.

19
00:01:41.282 --> 00:01:42.799
I'm gonna lose the race.

20
00:01:42.824 --> 00:01:44.588
Race? What race?

21
00:01:44.989 --> 00:01:46.050
We finally won!

22
00:01:46.051 --> 00:01:48.050
We won! We won!

23
00:01:53.434 --> 00:01:54.434
Aang.

24
00:01:54.957 --> 00:01:56.292
as an airbender.

25
00:01:56.317 --> 00:01:59.367
it's important that you
know when to show restraint.

26
00:02:00.124 --> 00:02:02.928
Even if you have the power to win.

27
00:02:02.952 --> 00:02:04.906
you are the Avatar.

28
00:02:04.931 --> 00:02:08.727
A lot of people are going to rely on you.

29
00:02:20.601 --> 00:02:21.391
He's gone!

30
00:02:21.416 --> 00:02:22.455
He ran away!

31
00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:24.090
What? I'm here!

32
00:02:24.814 --> 00:02:26.090
Where's the Avatar?

33
00:02:26.167 --> 00:02:27.167
Avatar!

34
00:02:27.519 --> 00:02:29.289
Aang. where are you?

35
00:02:29.847 --> 00:02:31.623
Gyatso. I'm here!

36
00:02:34.994 --> 00:02:37.110
I'm right here!

37
00:02:37.354 --> 00:02:39.110
I'm here!

38
00:02:39.135 --> 00:02:40.548
I'm here!

39
00:02:41.390 --> 00:02:42.390
I'm here.

40
00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:47.850
Hi. Momo.

41
00:02:48.666 --> 00:02:49.816
Hi. Appa.

42
00:02:50.305 --> 00:02:51.305
Was I asleep for long?

43
00:02:51.330 --> 00:02:52.635
Ooh! Okay. okay.

44
00:02:52.660 --> 00:02:54.106
I'm awake already.

45
00:02:54.355 --> 00:02:55.355
I know. I know.

46
00:02:55.380 --> 00:02:57.130
We've got a job to finish.

47
00:02:58.330 --> 00:03:00.130
Let's continue our journey.

48
00:03:00.505 --> 00:03:02.130
Back to our old home.

49
00:03:49.942 --> 00:03:51.422
This may not have been our best trip.

50
00:03:51.655 --> 00:03:54.462
but any Airbender relic we
find makes it all worthwhile.

51
00:04:00.204 --> 00:04:02.904
This could be the oldest
piece in our collection.

52
00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:09.350
Sonum.

53
00:04:22.642 --> 00:04:23.642
I miss you.

54
00:04:30.251 --> 00:04:32.035
Momo. go outside with Appa.

55
00:04:34.076 --> 00:04:35.076
Now!

56
00:04:44.199 --> 00:04:45.176
Who are you?

57
00:04:45.201 --> 00:04:46.508
Why are you doing this?

58
00:04:50.527 --> 00:04:51.580
Please. Stop.

59
00:04:51.668 --> 00:04:52.942
I don't want to hurt you.

60
00:04:57.220 --> 00:04:58.348
Where is it?

61
00:04:58.373 --> 00:04:59.591
No. that's not it.

62
00:04:59.616 --> 00:05:01.404
Hey. those are antiques.

63
00:05:12.987 --> 00:05:13.987
Enough!

64
00:05:17.279 --> 00:05:17.672
Wait!

65
00:05:18.112 --> 00:05:19.112
I found it!

66
00:05:21.413 --> 00:05:23.448
Sonum. why an after you?

67
00:05:42.623 --> 00:05:43.623
Wait!

68
00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:48.991
No. that's 1.000 years old!

69
00:05:54.863 --> 00:05:56.688
Why don't we just talk?
Maybe I can help.

70
00:05:56.713 --> 00:05:58.994
We don't need your help. Avatar.

71
00:05:59.541 --> 00:06:03.354
We're done living in a world where benders
have all the power and we have none.

72
00:06:03.379 --> 00:06:04.484
Who are you?

73
00:06:04.509 --> 00:06:05.764
We're the Denied.

74
00:06:05.789 --> 00:06:06.852
The Denied?

75
00:06:07.412 --> 00:06:08.401
Just kill him already!

76
00:06:08.426 --> 00:06:10.310
No! He'll bring the whole place down!

77
00:06:38.069 --> 00:06:39.489
You saved me.

78
00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:43.557
Kalik. wrap the map! Let's go!

79
00:06:57.348 --> 00:06:58.348
Oh. no!

80
00:07:55.999 --> 00:07:56.999
I'm fine.

81
00:07:57.139 --> 00:07:58.592
Momo. I'm fine.

82
00:08:01.480 --> 00:08:03.503
We've got to get to Republic City.

83
00:08:04.662 --> 00:08:05.862
Appa. yip. yip!

84
00:08:23.481 --> 00:08:24.481
Water.

85
00:08:25.186 --> 00:08:27.491
her tribes gather strength
from the moon

86
00:08:29.069 --> 00:08:30.749
and flow with the tides.

87
00:08:32.371 --> 00:08:33.477
Earth.

88
00:08:33.897 --> 00:08:36.333
a kingdomof unshakable will.

89
00:08:36.527 --> 00:08:38.927
Reliable and strong.

90
00:08:42.444 --> 00:08:43.444
Fire.

91
00:08:44.565 --> 00:08:47.539
a nation capable
of great destruction.

92
00:08:48.216 --> 00:08:51.470
but also of great warmth.

93
00:08:53.833 --> 00:08:54.833
Air.

94
00:08:55.121 --> 00:08:57.933
peaceful nomads with
the power of a hurricane.

95
00:08:58.433 --> 00:09:00.837
but the spirit of a gentle breeze.

96
00:09:03.169 --> 00:09:05.905
For generations. the Avatar.

97
00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:10.904
the one master of all four elements.
kept the nations in balance.

98
00:09:12.608 --> 00:09:17.010
But when that responsibility
fell to me as a child. I ran away.

99
00:09:17.563 --> 00:09:19.650
I was caught in a deadly storm.

100
00:09:20.295 --> 00:09:23.521
but my Avatar spirit preserved
me in a sphere of energy

101
00:09:23.546 --> 00:09:26.733
where I stayed for 100 years.

102
00:09:27.532 --> 00:09:31.495
I woke to discover that the
balance preserved by the Avatar

103
00:09:31.495 --> 00:09:33.772
had been destroyed by war.

104
00:09:34.773 --> 00:09:36.758
The air nomads were gone.

105
00:09:37.623 --> 00:09:38.623
All but one.

106
00:09:39.357 --> 00:09:40.357
Me.

107
00:09:41.144 --> 00:09:44.530
I could no longer run for my
responsibility as the Avatar.

108
00:09:45.806 --> 00:09:47.966
I found allies from every nation.

109
00:09:48.606 --> 00:09:51.370
Benders and non-benders.

110
00:09:52.884 --> 00:09:54.767
Katara taught me how to waterbend.

111
00:09:55.701 --> 00:09:58.478
Toph trained me in the
ways of the earthbenders.

112
00:09:59.111 --> 00:10:03.550
Zuko. once my worst enemy.
became my firebending teacher.

113
00:10:04.450 --> 00:10:08.906
Sokka showed me that bravery is the
most important part of being a leader.

114
00:10:10.280 --> 00:10:12.206
We became a family.

115
00:10:13.187 --> 00:10:16.552
And together.
we ended the Hundred Year War.

116
00:10:17.852 --> 00:10:22.570
Then. we began the hard
work of rebuilding the world.

117
00:10:34.125 --> 00:10:37.894
For so long.
the nations stood apart. alone.

118
00:10:37.919 --> 00:10:40.050
and we all suffered as a result.

119
00:10:40.319 --> 00:10:43.106
But here. on this ancient site.

120
00:10:43.131 --> 00:10:46.146
we created a place where all people are
welcome.

121
00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:48.704
bender and non-bender alike.

122
00:10:48.729 --> 00:10:52.244
working together in
peace to build the future.

123
00:10:52.619 --> 00:10:55.964
Though there are still those
who would seek to divide us.

124
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:57.590
we remain united.

125
00:10:58.239 --> 00:11:00.064
As a council representative.

126
00:11:00.089 --> 00:11:05.222
I am honored to be here today celebrating
the anniversary of Republic City

127
00:11:05.247 --> 00:11:10.006
and the opening of Unity Tower.
a symbol for all people.

128
00:11:17.841 --> 00:11:18.841
Yeah!

129
00:11:19.105 --> 00:11:20.610
It's the Avatar!

130
00:11:32.151 --> 00:11:33.151
Momo!

131
00:11:35.783 --> 00:11:36.990
Appa!

132
00:11:37.334 --> 00:11:39.418
I missed you. too. old friend.

133
00:11:41.559 --> 00:11:42.433
Aang!

134
00:11:42.486 --> 00:11:43.486
Katara!

135
00:11:48.644 --> 00:11:49.650
You're hurt.

136
00:11:57.780 --> 00:11:58.780
Take a deep breath.

137
00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:03.819
and exhale.

138
00:12:05.078 --> 00:12:07.247
I've heard the Denied
are growing in numbers.

139
00:12:07.272 --> 00:12:09.278
but they've never done anything like this.

140
00:12:09.303 --> 00:12:10.891
Attacking the Avatar?

141
00:12:10.916 --> 00:12:11.916
Yeah.

142
00:12:12.219 --> 00:12:13.809
They were incredible fighters.

143
00:12:14.479 --> 00:12:15.530
even without bending.

144
00:12:16.543 --> 00:12:17.582
Ahh. Ow!

145
00:12:17.607 --> 00:12:18.607
Oops!

146
00:12:18.835 --> 00:12:20.061
Breathe through it.

147
00:12:20.569 --> 00:12:22.453
Be honest. You're enjoying this.

148
00:12:22.478 --> 00:12:24.701
Aang. this is serious.

149
00:12:24.726 --> 00:12:26.692
Whatever this map they took was.

150
00:12:26.692 --> 00:12:29.464
if they were willing
to kill the Avatar to get it.

151
00:12:29.489 --> 00:12:31.151
what else are they willing to do?

152
00:12:31.668 --> 00:12:32.668
I don't know.

153
00:12:33.794 --> 00:12:35.389
I'm worried about you.

154
00:12:36.039 --> 00:12:39.970
You're spending more and
more time at the Air Temple. alone.

155
00:12:40.928 --> 00:12:43.856
It's how I hold on to my past.

156
00:12:45.689 --> 00:12:47.968
I know how hard this is for you.

157
00:12:52.209 --> 00:12:53.710
When I was attacked.

158
00:12:54.525 --> 00:12:56.709
all I could think about was that...

159
00:12:57.287 --> 00:12:59.095
this could be it.

160
00:13:00.459 --> 00:13:03.292
I'm the last Airbender.

161
00:13:04.463 --> 00:13:05.710
If I die.

162
00:13:06.353 --> 00:13:08.449
my culture dies with me.

163
00:13:11.229 --> 00:13:13.338
You may be the last Airbender.

164
00:13:13.679 --> 00:13:15.730
but you're not alone.

165
00:13:16.271 --> 00:13:17.271
Aang.

166
00:13:17.379 --> 00:13:19.710
None of this would exist without you.

167
00:13:20.979 --> 00:13:24.905
You made the city possible
with your heart and your mind.

168
00:13:26.305 --> 00:13:28.058
Because of you.

169
00:13:28.082 --> 00:13:30.988
all of the nations live here. together.

170
00:13:33.602 --> 00:13:35.091
All except mine.

171
00:13:45.381 --> 00:13:49.730
I know. but the people here
still need your protection.

172
00:13:50.264 --> 00:13:51.944
You're an Airbender.

173
00:13:52.829 --> 00:13:54.730
but you're also the Avatar.

174
00:13:56.979 --> 00:13:57.979
You're right.

175
00:13:59.529 --> 00:14:03.462
Whoever this Sonum person is.
I need to find out more.

176
00:14:29.214 --> 00:14:30.214
Aang.

177
00:14:30.477 --> 00:14:31.477
Avatar Roku.

178
00:14:31.800 --> 00:14:33.770
It is good to see you again.

179
00:14:34.151 --> 00:14:35.323
How can I help you?

180
00:14:35.605 --> 00:14:40.094
In your lifetime. did you ever hear of
an ancient Airbender named Sonum?

181
00:14:40.119 --> 00:14:44.340
I have not.
but you have many past lives to call upon.

182
00:14:44.739 --> 00:14:48.790
Perhaps one further back in
the Avatar cycle can help you.

183
00:14:49.464 --> 00:14:50.790
Thank you. Avatar Roku.

184
00:14:52.790 --> 00:14:55.790
- I'm sorry.
- I've never heard of Sonum.

185
00:14:55.939 --> 00:14:57.790
- Perhaps earlier.
- You must go find him.

186
00:14:57.791 --> 00:14:58.791
Not here. Not here.

187
00:15:08.993 --> 00:15:10.810
Um. hello?

188
00:15:11.732 --> 00:15:13.167
Is there anyone here?

189
00:15:14.459 --> 00:15:15.810
Hello?

190
00:15:17.811 --> 00:15:22.830
Who calls upon Avatar Xion.
vast wealth of knowledge

191
00:15:26.853 --> 00:15:28.166
Oh. hello.

192
00:15:28.486 --> 00:15:31.830
You look like an Avatar from
a time quite distant from mine.

193
00:15:32.029 --> 00:15:35.092
Please. please.
tell me about your era.

194
00:15:35.117 --> 00:15:36.806
What are people wearing?

195
00:15:36.831 --> 00:15:38.204
Are sandals still a thing?

196
00:15:38.229 --> 00:15:39.830
Uh. yes.

197
00:15:40.229 --> 00:15:41.644
Why? Why?

198
00:15:41.669 --> 00:15:47.590
After so many years. open toes.
in someone else's crusty cuticles.

199
00:15:48.066 --> 00:15:49.065
Disgusting.

200
00:15:49.090 --> 00:15:50.090
Right.

201
00:15:50.236 --> 00:15:52.577
Anyway. I have come through guidance.

202
00:15:52.615 --> 00:15:54.124
You see. I was attacked.

203
00:15:54.149 --> 00:15:56.479
It was not me. okay?
It wasn't me.

204
00:15:56.504 --> 00:15:57.524
I know that.

205
00:15:57.549 --> 00:16:00.850
I think it might have something to do
with an Airbender named Sonum.

206
00:16:01.784 --> 00:16:04.357
Sonum. It sounds familiar.

207
00:16:04.749 --> 00:16:07.198
Sonum.
Where have I heard that name before?

208
00:16:08.404 --> 00:16:12.615
Sonum was the youngest daughter of the owner of
the possum chicken shop at the corner marketplace.

209
00:16:12.640 --> 00:16:15.470
Wait. That was my ex. Soniam.

210
00:16:15.495 --> 00:16:18.549
If only she didn't have
those humongous toenails.

211
00:16:18.615 --> 00:16:20.215
Ugh. Disgusting.

212
00:16:20.362 --> 00:16:21.483
This is going nowhere.

213
00:16:21.562 --> 00:16:23.516
Sonum?

214
00:16:23.869 --> 00:16:25.999
Well. thank you for your time.

215
00:16:26.024 --> 00:16:27.681
I must continue my search.

216
00:16:27.869 --> 00:16:29.955
Oh! Sonum!

217
00:16:30.062 --> 00:16:34.280
You're asking about the
legend of the lost Avatar.

218
00:16:34.311 --> 00:16:35.994
Sona m was an Avatar?

219
00:16:36.019 --> 00:16:37.941
Indeed she was.

220
00:16:37.966 --> 00:16:42.571
She was the Avatar in the
golden age of Airbender.

221
00:16:42.596 --> 00:16:48.296
Legend said she had a staff that could
channel the vast energy of the spirit world.

222
00:16:48.321 --> 00:16:51.468
granting its keeper unlimited power.

223
00:16:51.726 --> 00:16:54.516
Is... Is that even possible?

224
00:16:55.230 --> 00:16:57.164
We'll never know for sure.

225
00:16:57.208 --> 00:17:00.739
Many Avatars have tried to
communicate with her. but they couldn't.

226
00:17:00.764 --> 00:17:05.378
She disappeared so completely
that it was as if she never existed.

227
00:17:05.984 --> 00:17:07.691
And perhaps it's better that way.

228
00:17:08.277 --> 00:17:12.419
Maybe such a staff was too
dangerous for anyone to possess.

229
00:17:12.829 --> 00:17:14.433
Even the Avatar.

230
00:17:14.879 --> 00:17:17.125
But... But that's exactly
why I need to find it.

231
00:17:17.392 --> 00:17:19.930
The people who attacked
me discovered a map.

232
00:17:20.028 --> 00:17:21.588
It must lead to the staff.

233
00:17:22.079 --> 00:17:24.199
Avatar Xion. please.

234
00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:26.201
You have to tell me where it is.

235
00:17:28.854 --> 00:17:34.950
The legend says that Sonum disappeared
with her staff on the peak of Mount Baihu.

236
00:17:37.249 --> 00:17:39.950
Katara. I'm sorry to leave so suddenly.

237
00:17:40.249 --> 00:17:42.950
but I found out what the Denied are after.

238
00:17:43.299 --> 00:17:45.930
Sonim had a staff of immense power.

239
00:17:46.079 --> 00:17:49.930
And in their hands. it could
be a devastating weapon.

240
00:17:49.931 --> 00:17:51.930
They have a head start.

241
00:17:51.931 --> 00:17:53.829
There's no time to waste.

242
00:17:54.461 --> 00:17:57.457
You take Appa and Momo and
gather up the rest of the team.

243
00:17:57.482 --> 00:17:58.930
We're gonna need some help.

244
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:08.551
Next on the agenda.
a Fire Nation naval vessel

245
00:18:08.584 --> 00:18:12.474
came into conflict with an extremist
group of non-Benders called the Denied.

246
00:18:12.499 --> 00:18:14.110
They've been
robbing ancient sites...

247
00:18:14.134 --> 00:18:15.424
Your Majesty!

248
00:18:15.449 --> 00:18:17.950
An urgent message has
arrived from Republic City.

249
00:18:17.951 --> 00:18:18.951
How impudent.

250
00:18:19.399 --> 00:18:20.822
Can't you see Fire Lord Zuko is...

251
00:18:20.847 --> 00:18:22.091
Chamberlain.

252
00:18:23.219 --> 00:18:24.995
There's only one person
who can send a message

253
00:18:25.019 --> 00:18:27.059
urgent enough to interrupt
the Fire Lord's counsel.

254
00:18:27.769 --> 00:18:28.970
Is it from the Avatar?

255
00:18:28.971 --> 00:18:29.971
Yes. my lord.

256
00:18:30.070 --> 00:18:30.970
Read it to me.

257
00:18:30.971 --> 00:18:31.971
Yes. my lord.

258
00:18:35.319 --> 00:18:35.970
Um...

259
00:18:36.337 --> 00:18:37.337
What are you doing?

260
00:18:37.457 --> 00:18:38.457
Read it quickly.

261
00:18:38.655 --> 00:18:41.103
Uh. y-y-yes. Grand Chamberlain.

262
00:18:42.319 --> 00:18:45.437
Flameo Hartman.
house ruling the Fire Nation.

263
00:18:45.536 --> 00:18:47.991
I hope the boring Chamberlain
you mentioned...

264
00:18:48.016 --> 00:18:51.774
in your letters isn't
still annoying you.

265
00:18:51.799 --> 00:18:53.990
Anywho. to cut to the
chase. I need your help.

266
00:18:53.991 --> 00:18:57.217
Can you please come immediately?

267
00:18:57.242 --> 00:19:00.969
Oh. and don't forget to
bring some firecracker buns.

268
00:19:03.618 --> 00:19:06.236
Allow me to present Sokka Cycle.

269
00:19:06.261 --> 00:19:10.395
Flames launch you into the sky where
you can drop water bombs on your enemies.

270
00:19:10.420 --> 00:19:13.608
Then skis pop out to
help you stick the landing.

271
00:19:13.633 --> 00:19:15.010
Pretty great. right?

272
00:19:15.011 --> 00:19:16.101
Eh. boring.

273
00:19:16.126 --> 00:19:18.352
Why would you need a sled
when you can just waterbend?

274
00:19:18.412 --> 00:19:19.819
Oh. oh. oh. like me. like me!

275
00:19:19.866 --> 00:19:21.010
Whee!

276
00:19:21.259 --> 00:19:24.649
Keep in mind. there's still plenty
of folks like me who can't bend.

277
00:19:24.674 --> 00:19:27.286
Why would Avatar Aang
partner with a non-bender?

278
00:19:27.367 --> 00:19:28.734
Ugh. Why?

279
00:19:28.760 --> 00:19:29.907
I'll tell you why.

280
00:19:29.940 --> 00:19:32.091
I saved him from the iceberg.

281
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:36.062
My boomerang flew by his side while I
carried away enemies with my trusty blade.

282
00:19:36.095 --> 00:19:38.532
I even took down the whole
Fire Nation airship armada.

283
00:19:40.531 --> 00:19:43.671
And on top of all that. I
was more popular than him.

284
00:19:45.172 --> 00:19:46.525
You're such a liar. Sokka.

285
00:19:49.821 --> 00:19:50.916
It's from the Avatar.

286
00:19:51.049 --> 00:19:51.579
Wow!

287
00:19:51.604 --> 00:19:52.248
Really?

288
00:19:52.262 --> 00:19:52.895
Cool!

289
00:19:53.213 --> 00:19:54.702
Oh. so now you think I'm cool?

290
00:19:55.917 --> 00:19:57.650
All right. metalbenders.

291
00:19:58.164 --> 00:20:00.052
Let's see if any of you tenderfoots

292
00:20:00.199 --> 00:20:01.736
can at least make me use my hands.

293
00:20:35.091 --> 00:20:38.498
I'm still the greatest
earthbender in the world!

294
00:20:39.857 --> 00:20:41.020
And I'm bored.

295
00:20:41.306 --> 00:20:43.642
M-Master Toph.
there's a bird on your head.

296
00:20:43.789 --> 00:20:44.444
And?

297
00:20:44.539 --> 00:20:46.090
It looks like it has a message.

298
00:20:46.243 --> 00:20:46.876
Read.

299
00:20:47.115 --> 00:20:49.201
Uh. it's from Avatar Aang.

300
00:20:49.435 --> 00:20:50.435
He needs your help.

301
00:20:50.608 --> 00:20:51.608
It's the Denied?

302
00:20:52.197 --> 00:20:53.197
Where is he?

303
00:20:53.259 --> 00:20:54.724
Mount Bihu.

304
00:21:56.777 --> 00:21:58.209
No. no. no!

305
00:21:58.823 --> 00:21:59.823
No.

306
00:22:03.732 --> 00:22:04.999
I love that hat.

307
00:23:49.753 --> 00:23:50.786
Sonum?

308
00:23:56.004 --> 00:23:57.401
Could that be you?

309
00:25:00.795 --> 00:25:01.815
Who are you?

310
00:27:54.753 --> 00:27:55.753
Aang!

311
00:28:23.609 --> 00:28:25.669
Team avatar to the rescue.

312
00:28:27.451 --> 00:28:28.451
Aang.

313
00:28:29.285 --> 00:28:30.285
You made it.

314
00:28:30.344 --> 00:28:33.252
You couldn't wait a day before
running off to get yourself killed?

315
00:28:33.379 --> 00:28:35.179
I thought you were
here to looking for staff.

316
00:28:35.769 --> 00:28:36.896
Who is this guy?

317
00:28:44.072 --> 00:28:45.072
It Airbender

318
00:29:06.399 --> 00:29:08.643
How did he hold up an entire mountain?

319
00:29:08.857 --> 00:29:11.979
His chi is strong.
like nothing I've ever felt.

320
00:29:13.549 --> 00:29:18.350
Hey. Avatar. you think this guy beat
your record for longest frozen airbender?

321
00:29:18.399 --> 00:29:21.350
Yeah.
How long do you think he was in that ice?

322
00:29:21.549 --> 00:29:25.370
I don't know. His tattoos look ancient.

323
00:29:26.019 --> 00:29:27.728
He's been in there a long time.

324
00:29:28.108 --> 00:29:29.522
He smells good for an old guy.

325
00:29:29.622 --> 00:29:30.199
Ew.

326
00:29:30.258 --> 00:29:32.378
What? My senses tell me
this guy is pretty attractive.

327
00:29:32.419 --> 00:29:33.699
- Toph!
- Someone else confirmed.

328
00:29:33.732 --> 00:29:34.479
This is serious.

329
00:29:34.552 --> 00:29:35.988
What does "attractive" even mean?

330
00:29:36.014 --> 00:29:37.370
Just give me a straight confirmation.

331
00:29:37.371 --> 00:29:38.449
Is he attractive?

332
00:29:38.529 --> 00:29:39.371
He's very attractive.

333
00:29:39.529 --> 00:29:40.529
Huh?

334
00:29:41.469 --> 00:29:44.509
What? He is.
It's all in the bone structure.

335
00:29:45.022 --> 00:29:46.036
No.

336
00:29:46.391 --> 00:29:47.391
No.

337
00:29:47.670 --> 00:29:48.670
No!

338
00:29:49.340 --> 00:29:50.024
NO!

339
00:29:50.049 --> 00:29:51.847
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey.

340
00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:53.720
Easy. You're safe.

341
00:29:56.579 --> 00:29:57.319
Earthbender!

342
00:29:57.344 --> 00:29:58.879
No. no. no. We're all friends here.

343
00:29:59.292 --> 00:30:00.391
It's okay.

344
00:30:00.416 --> 00:30:03.373
Someone woke up on the
wrong side of the mountain.

345
00:30:03.909 --> 00:30:05.461
Where is she?

346
00:30:06.609 --> 00:30:08.410
Where is Avatar Sonum?

347
00:30:08.709 --> 00:30:09.709
You knew Sonum?

348
00:30:11.309 --> 00:30:12.410
Who are you?

349
00:30:13.609 --> 00:30:15.483
I don't know how to explain it.

350
00:30:15.507 --> 00:30:17.660
but you've been asleep for a long time.

351
00:30:19.034 --> 00:30:20.410
I'm the Avatar now.

352
00:30:20.959 --> 00:30:21.959
I'm Aang.

353
00:30:23.192 --> 00:30:25.339
If you're the Avatar.

354
00:30:25.363 --> 00:30:27.790
then Sonum.

355
00:30:30.729 --> 00:30:34.844
Well. Sonum might be long gone.
but on the bright side.

356
00:30:34.869 --> 00:30:37.049
you woke up at the perfect time.

357
00:30:37.074 --> 00:30:39.797
Everyone will be amazed
to see another Airbender.

358
00:30:39.822 --> 00:30:42.430
Aang's not the last one anymore.

359
00:30:43.329 --> 00:30:45.271
What do you mean. "last"?

360
00:30:45.885 --> 00:30:46.885
Oh.

361
00:30:49.828 --> 00:30:51.329
The Air Nomads.

362
00:30:52.149 --> 00:30:53.214
They've been wiped out.

363
00:30:55.149 --> 00:30:56.149
There's only me.

364
00:30:58.296 --> 00:30:59.296
No.

365
00:31:00.199 --> 00:31:02.609
Sonum Staff. do you have it?

366
00:31:03.649 --> 00:31:04.816
It's our only hope now.

367
00:31:05.682 --> 00:31:06.682
What do you mean?

368
00:31:07.069 --> 00:31:08.470
I thought it was a weapon.

369
00:31:09.748 --> 00:31:11.349
The staff is no weapon.

370
00:31:12.269 --> 00:31:13.269
It is a gift.

371
00:31:15.937 --> 00:31:20.902
<i>With it. Sonum was able to channel
the vast power of the spirit world.</i>

372
00:31:21.569 --> 00:31:24.961
<i>It was this power
that allowed Jirana to flourish.</i>

373
00:31:25.549 --> 00:31:28.014
<i>The greatest city in the world.</i>

374
00:31:28.038 --> 00:31:30.039
<i>an Air Nomad utopia.</i>

375
00:31:30.064 --> 00:31:34.069
<i>where Sonum presided
over a golden age of balance.</i>

376
00:31:34.094 --> 00:31:37.429
<i>and where I devoted my life
to serving her.</i>

377
00:31:37.865 --> 00:31:42.287
<i>In return. she raised me up
and used her staff to give me.</i>

378
00:31:42.352 --> 00:31:46.982
<i>a lowly non-Bender.
the power to bend the air.</i>

379
00:31:47.609 --> 00:31:50.510
<i>I was the first.
but I would not be the last.</i>

380
00:31:51.419 --> 00:31:54.266
<i>She filled the skies
with Airbenders.</i>

381
00:31:54.291 --> 00:31:57.928
<i>and we flew by her side.
spreading peace across the world.</i>

382
00:32:06.959 --> 00:32:08.990
Aang. are you okay?

383
00:32:10.632 --> 00:32:13.383
Sonum used the staff
to give people Airbending.

384
00:32:14.292 --> 00:32:16.014
If we found it.

385
00:32:17.479 --> 00:32:20.042
I could bring Airbending back to the world.

386
00:32:20.964 --> 00:32:21.870
This is incredible.

387
00:32:21.895 --> 00:32:24.625
There haven't been Airbenders
for over a hundred years.

388
00:32:25.325 --> 00:32:28.292
This is everything you ever wanted. Aang.

389
00:32:29.799 --> 00:32:33.550
We could heal the greatest atrocity
my nation committed in the war.

390
00:32:34.749 --> 00:32:37.668
This could be the final step
to rebuilding the world.

391
00:32:37.949 --> 00:32:39.883
Not if the Denied get there first.

392
00:32:39.908 --> 00:32:41.185
They have the map.

393
00:32:42.249 --> 00:32:43.632
Who are the Denied?

394
00:32:43.657 --> 00:32:45.550
A group of violent non-Benders.

395
00:32:45.949 --> 00:32:46.894
They...

396
00:32:46.918 --> 00:32:50.394
they must be after the staff
to give themselves Airbending.

397
00:32:50.419 --> 00:32:52.144
Then there's no time to waste.

398
00:32:52.169 --> 00:32:54.147
There's only one place it could be.

399
00:32:54.172 --> 00:32:55.253
Ready your bison.

400
00:32:55.278 --> 00:32:58.169
We'll need to travel
across the endless ocean.

401
00:32:58.194 --> 00:33:00.046
On the other side of the world?

402
00:33:00.071 --> 00:33:01.409
But there's nothing out there.

403
00:33:01.434 --> 00:33:02.871
There's an island.

404
00:33:02.895 --> 00:33:04.894
The journey will not be easy.

405
00:33:04.919 --> 00:33:06.590
but we can make it.

406
00:33:07.439 --> 00:33:08.590
Then let's get going.

407
00:33:10.032 --> 00:33:12.758
The skies are no place for a water child.

408
00:33:12.783 --> 00:33:14.477
Water child?

409
00:33:14.864 --> 00:33:18.490
Um. I know you just
woke up after thousands of years.

410
00:33:18.515 --> 00:33:20.459
but we do these things together.

411
00:33:20.484 --> 00:33:21.626
Trust me.

412
00:33:21.651 --> 00:33:22.964
we're stronger this way.

413
00:33:22.989 --> 00:33:24.820
Welcome to Team Avatar.

414
00:33:25.239 --> 00:33:26.459
What's your name?

415
00:33:27.139 --> 00:33:28.438
Taga.

416
00:33:28.462 --> 00:33:30.583
My name is Taga.

417
00:33:40.012 --> 00:33:42.590
Just think of it as a big metal air bison.

418
00:33:50.650 --> 00:33:54.079
<i>We will travel ancient
paths through the sky.</i>

419
00:33:55.444 --> 00:33:59.185
<i>ones that our people learned
by following the great air bison herds</i>

420
00:33:59.185 --> 00:34:01.518
<i>that long ago taught us Airbending.</i>

421
00:34:02.020 --> 00:34:04.640
<i>Air currents known only to us.</i>

422
00:34:04.664 --> 00:34:07.934
<i>encircling the great sphere of existence.</i>

423
00:34:08.311 --> 00:34:11.180
<i>allowing us to travel where we wish.</i>

424
00:34:11.204 --> 00:34:15.220
<i>giving us our name.
the Air Nomads.</i>

425
00:34:44.780 --> 00:34:46.230
What's he doing?

426
00:34:46.880 --> 00:34:48.926
He's really feeling that air.

427
00:34:49.730 --> 00:34:51.800
He's navigating by instinct.

428
00:34:51.825 --> 00:34:54.099
What if his instincts are just wrong?

429
00:34:54.124 --> 00:34:56.668
Who needs instincts
when you've got muscles like that?

430
00:34:56.693 --> 00:34:59.448
Or what if his brain is messed up
from being frozen?

431
00:34:59.473 --> 00:35:00.335
Like me?

432
00:35:00.360 --> 00:35:02.486
Uh. no. no!

433
00:35:02.511 --> 00:35:05.213
He was frozen for 5.000 years. okay?

434
00:35:05.238 --> 00:35:07.204
You were frozen for. what. 100?

435
00:35:07.229 --> 00:35:08.216
Okay. that's nothing.

436
00:35:08.240 --> 00:35:10.172
Your brain is...

437
00:35:10.196 --> 00:35:11.279
fresh.

438
00:35:11.856 --> 00:35:15.095
Maybe he is a little
old-fashioned. but look at him.

439
00:35:15.120 --> 00:35:16.890
He's so in tune with his element.

440
00:35:16.915 --> 00:35:21.916
he can travel across the entire ocean
with no map. no instruments.

441
00:35:24.671 --> 00:35:26.670
There's so much I can learn from him.

442
00:35:38.433 --> 00:35:42.026
I'd give anything to be able
to see my air bison again.

443
00:35:45.344 --> 00:35:47.203
And now.

444
00:35:47.227 --> 00:35:48.980
to see only one remains.

445
00:35:51.280 --> 00:35:52.280
Aang.

446
00:35:53.190 --> 00:35:55.626
You said our people
were wiped out.

447
00:35:55.650 --> 00:35:56.904
yet you survived.

448
00:35:57.540 --> 00:35:58.540
How?

449
00:36:00.610 --> 00:36:02.710
I had just found out
I was the Avatar.

450
00:36:04.471 --> 00:36:06.300
but the responsibility...

451
00:36:06.324 --> 00:36:07.710
it was too much.

452
00:36:09.224 --> 00:36:10.549
So I ran away.

453
00:36:11.990 --> 00:36:13.816
And while I was gone.

454
00:36:13.840 --> 00:36:15.496
the Fire Nation attacked.

455
00:36:17.763 --> 00:36:19.222
They were looking for me.

456
00:36:21.622 --> 00:36:22.908
If...

457
00:36:22.932 --> 00:36:24.730
If I'd just been there...

458
00:36:25.136 --> 00:36:26.645
Sonum would say.

459
00:36:26.930 --> 00:36:29.730
Air nomads are formed
from the mist.

460
00:36:30.230 --> 00:36:32.730
We walk the world
for a moment in time.

461
00:36:33.130 --> 00:36:36.425
Then we return
to the eternal wind.

462
00:36:37.950 --> 00:36:39.598
Monkiatsu taught me that.

463
00:36:40.650 --> 00:36:42.343
We carry the same weight.

464
00:36:42.650 --> 00:36:45.750
a grief no one else could
possibly comprehend.

465
00:36:45.950 --> 00:36:48.757
But you and I can heal the past.

466
00:36:49.128 --> 00:36:52.653
Let me show you how powerful
our element can be

467
00:36:52.653 --> 00:36:55.004
when airbenders work together.

468
00:36:58.802 --> 00:37:00.247
What are you doing?!

469
00:37:01.214 --> 00:37:03.086
This is how Sonum taught me!

470
00:37:03.489 --> 00:37:05.770
Feel the energy that tethers us.

471
00:37:11.324 --> 00:37:12.946
The bond between us...

472
00:37:12.970 --> 00:37:14.302
can you feel it?

473
00:37:14.326 --> 00:37:15.326
Use it!

474
00:37:15.505 --> 00:37:17.080
This is amazing!

475
00:37:22.182 --> 00:37:23.483
Whoo-hoo!

476
00:37:23.508 --> 00:37:24.817
Oh. yeah!

477
00:37:24.842 --> 00:37:26.148
Human boomerang!

478
00:37:26.173 --> 00:37:27.912
He's actually flying.

479
00:37:27.937 --> 00:37:28.852
So are we.

480
00:37:28.877 --> 00:37:31.283
Whoa! That's my best friend!
That's my best friend!

481
00:37:32.550 --> 00:37:34.136
No. you throw me!

482
00:38:02.194 --> 00:38:04.786
I had no idea this was possible!

483
00:38:04.811 --> 00:38:06.434
This is only the beginning.

484
00:38:13.969 --> 00:38:15.589
I can't believe it.

485
00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:18.525
Airbenders will fill the sky again.

486
00:38:18.550 --> 00:38:20.850
We have been given a great gift...

487
00:38:21.163 --> 00:38:23.085
the chance to redeem ourselves.

488
00:38:23.800 --> 00:38:26.468
You were destined to find
me on that mountain. Aang.

489
00:38:28.650 --> 00:38:29.974
How did you end up there?

490
00:38:34.163 --> 00:38:36.850
The earthbenders had attacked Tirana.

491
00:38:37.010 --> 00:38:39.730
Sonum and I fought
fearlessly. side by side.

492
00:38:40.413 --> 00:38:42.239
We drove them back to Mount Bahu.

493
00:38:42.593 --> 00:38:44.781
and that's the last I remember.

494
00:38:46.490 --> 00:38:48.344
She must have saved your life.

495
00:38:48.820 --> 00:38:51.870
Only an Avatar could
have put you in that sphere.

496
00:38:55.020 --> 00:38:57.831
Aang. can I ask you something?

497
00:38:58.224 --> 00:38:59.224
Of course.

498
00:38:59.740 --> 00:39:02.890
If the Fire Nation
destroyed the Air Nomads.

499
00:39:03.384 --> 00:39:06.890
how can you suffer the
presence of the Fire Lord?

500
00:39:09.240 --> 00:39:11.424
Zuko is a friend and an ally.

501
00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:14.808
He turned against his own
father to help me end the war.

502
00:39:15.263 --> 00:39:17.557
Yet he wears the crown himself now.

503
00:39:18.560 --> 00:39:21.910
Fire. by its nature. burns. Aang.

504
00:39:22.260 --> 00:39:25.843
Our kind have always suffered
at the hands of the other elements.

505
00:39:27.210 --> 00:39:29.315
That's why we built Republic City...

506
00:39:29.710 --> 00:39:32.285
to show the world that
if we listen to each other.

507
00:39:32.310 --> 00:39:34.809
we can all live together in peace.

508
00:39:36.178 --> 00:39:38.498
And once we bring back airbenders.

509
00:39:38.876 --> 00:39:40.045
it'll be complete.

510
00:39:43.730 --> 00:39:45.340
When everyone stuck to their own.

511
00:39:45.880 --> 00:39:48.239
the whole world was nearly torn apart.

512
00:39:49.030 --> 00:39:53.251
And besides. Katara.
Sokka. Zuko. Toph.

513
00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:54.930
they're my family now.

514
00:39:56.430 --> 00:39:58.950
I want to live in a world
where we can all be together.

515
00:40:00.850 --> 00:40:03.528
You remind me so much of Sonum.

516
00:40:07.931 --> 00:40:09.270
It's the Avatar.

517
00:40:09.538 --> 00:40:11.766
And this time.
he's got his friends with them.

518
00:40:11.791 --> 00:40:13.576
That's the Fire Lord's airship.

519
00:40:13.601 --> 00:40:14.903
How'd they get ahead of us?

520
00:40:14.928 --> 00:40:16.359
They don't even have the map.

521
00:40:16.384 --> 00:40:18.897
We can't risk him
getting to the staff first.

522
00:40:18.922 --> 00:40:19.484
Kill him.

523
00:40:19.509 --> 00:40:21.046
But he spared our lives.

524
00:40:21.688 --> 00:40:25.218
And how many Countless were killed in
the hundred years waiting for his return?

525
00:40:25.243 --> 00:40:28.012
Where was he when
your family was wiped out?

526
00:40:28.037 --> 00:40:32.401
If we want anything to change.
we need what the benders have... power.

527
00:40:40.762 --> 00:40:41.762
Fire!

528
00:40:48.209 --> 00:40:49.209
It's the Denied.

529
00:40:51.636 --> 00:40:53.867
Uh. we are definitely under attack.

530
00:40:55.753 --> 00:40:57.048
Turn up your spreads.

531
00:41:10.144 --> 00:41:11.844
Is he crushing the ship?

532
00:41:13.758 --> 00:41:14.758
Taga?

533
00:41:15.729 --> 00:41:16.729
Taga. stop!

534
00:41:42.365 --> 00:41:43.365
We're here.

535
00:41:45.771 --> 00:41:46.968
The Immortal Storm.

536
00:41:48.142 --> 00:41:49.142
Oh. no.

537
00:41:54.637 --> 00:41:56.792
There has to be another way around.

538
00:41:56.817 --> 00:41:59.519
No. Together.
you and I can clear a path for the ship.

539
00:41:59.544 --> 00:42:01.090
But we have to go now.

540
00:42:01.989 --> 00:42:03.886
Aang. trust me.

541
00:42:07.485 --> 00:42:09.932
Uh. maybe now's a good time to turn back.

542
00:42:09.957 --> 00:42:11.799
I don't think that's an option anymore.

543
00:42:12.062 --> 00:42:13.524
Where are they going?

544
00:42:22.063 --> 00:42:24.363
The engine's out.
We're losing air pressure.

545
00:42:30.432 --> 00:42:31.788
Katara. come with me.

546
00:42:31.813 --> 00:42:32.646
What about me?

547
00:42:32.671 --> 00:42:33.532
Take the wheel.

548
00:42:33.557 --> 00:42:36.554
What? I've only ever
crashed Fire Nation airships.

549
00:42:38.287 --> 00:42:39.695
Okay. let's see.
Here's our rudder.

550
00:42:39.720 --> 00:42:41.453
This is the elevator.
There's our ballast.

551
00:42:41.478 --> 00:42:44.278
And there's the giant tornado
that's going to kill us all.

552
00:42:47.410 --> 00:42:48.810
Follow my lead.

553
00:43:00.144 --> 00:43:01.224
Work with me.

554
00:43:01.249 --> 00:43:02.572
Just like I showed you.

555
00:43:03.204 --> 00:43:04.204
We can heart it.

556
00:43:14.604 --> 00:43:17.720
Yes! That's it. Aang.
Keep going.

557
00:43:29.835 --> 00:43:30.835
Got it.

558
00:43:34.055 --> 00:43:36.095
Zuko! Zuko!

559
00:43:36.120 --> 00:43:39.318
Aang and Taga are destroying tornadoes.
but there's too many!

560
00:43:39.343 --> 00:43:40.786
And they're everywhere!

561
00:43:40.811 --> 00:43:41.910
Just steer the ship.

562
00:43:41.934 --> 00:43:42.946
Don't lose Aang.

563
00:43:42.971 --> 00:43:46.766
It's not that easy.
especially when everything is sideways.

564
00:43:46.793 --> 00:43:48.108
Okay. left!

565
00:43:57.480 --> 00:43:58.555
I did it!

566
00:43:59.413 --> 00:44:00.413
Right!

567
00:44:08.850 --> 00:44:10.656
Oh no. we're falling behind!

568
00:44:11.988 --> 00:44:13.353
I'm losing sight of them.

569
00:44:13.377 --> 00:44:14.657
We have to go back.

570
00:44:14.682 --> 00:44:16.155
Trust in your friends.

571
00:44:16.155 --> 00:44:18.384
They won't make it
 if we don't clear a path.

572
00:44:31.719 --> 00:44:33.920
Zuko. we're going to crash into the sea!

573
00:44:33.945 --> 00:44:36.888
When I give you the signal.
pull the lever next to the wheel.

574
00:44:41.259 --> 00:44:43.199
We're going to crash!
We're going to crash!

575
00:44:43.668 --> 00:44:44.668
Katara?

576
00:45:04.634 --> 00:45:06.454
Give me the signal!
Give me the signal!

577
00:45:11.303 --> 00:45:12.303
Closed!

578
00:45:13.804 --> 00:45:14.937
Sokka. now!

579
00:45:15.490 --> 00:45:16.795
Here we go!

580
00:45:39.338 --> 00:45:41.322
Katara! We did it!

581
00:45:42.347 --> 00:45:43.654
What were you thinking?

582
00:45:43.692 --> 00:45:45.481
I was clearing the tornadoes 
to make a path.

583
00:45:45.506 --> 00:45:48.184
The ship almost crashed. Aang.
We could have died.

584
00:45:48.209 --> 00:45:51.239
And what if you got yourself killed?
You're the Avatar.

585
00:45:51.264 --> 00:45:54.189
This is too risky.
We need to turn back now.

586
00:45:54.214 --> 00:45:55.227
No!

587
00:45:55.251 --> 00:45:56.760
We're almost there.

588
00:45:56.918 --> 00:45:59.398
We just need to get
to the eye of the storm.

589
00:45:59.899 --> 00:46:01.291
Aang. no!

590
00:46:01.315 --> 00:46:02.791
This is too dangerous.

591
00:46:02.816 --> 00:46:04.007
The staff is out there.

592
00:46:04.031 --> 00:46:05.493
They denied her after it.

593
00:46:05.518 --> 00:46:08.038
Do you really believe that they
could make it through the storm?

594
00:46:08.063 --> 00:46:11.422
We're nearly there.
That staff can bring back my people.

595
00:46:11.447 --> 00:46:12.897
I understand how much you want that. but...

596
00:46:12.921 --> 00:46:15.137
You don't understand.
None of you do.

597
00:46:16.492 --> 00:46:17.831
Aang...

598
00:46:19.522 --> 00:46:21.053
We push forward.

599
00:46:24.702 --> 00:46:27.669
If we generate enough air.
we can push our way through.

600
00:47:12.898 --> 00:47:14.269
We're alive?

601
00:47:14.446 --> 00:47:15.815
We made it through.

602
00:47:15.839 --> 00:47:17.045
Thank you. Taga.

603
00:47:17.070 --> 00:47:19.970
It was you. Aang.
We're here because of you.

604
00:47:19.995 --> 00:47:21.829
Yeah. we're having a good time. too.

605
00:47:21.854 --> 00:47:24.220
You could have told us we were
flying into the Immortal Storm.

606
00:47:24.245 --> 00:47:26.995
I know it was dangerous but.
we had to risk it.

607
00:47:27.020 --> 00:47:27.734
We?

608
00:47:28.171 --> 00:47:30.387
I don't remember
when we took a vote on that.

609
00:47:30.411 --> 00:47:32.307
There wasn't time.
I had to make a call.

610
00:47:32.332 --> 00:47:34.174
Friends. please. don't blame Aang.

611
00:47:34.618 --> 00:47:36.191
This is all my fault.

612
00:47:36.215 --> 00:47:37.949
I knew this would be difficult.

613
00:47:38.870 --> 00:47:41.360
But Aang believed in
your strength as a team.

614
00:47:41.543 --> 00:47:43.575
And I'm honored to be a part of it.

615
00:47:49.523 --> 00:47:51.369
I forgive you. Taga.

616
00:47:51.620 --> 00:47:53.396
Everyone. look.

617
00:47:54.720 --> 00:47:56.345
These islands...

618
00:47:56.369 --> 00:47:57.535
they were...

619
00:47:57.559 --> 00:47:58.915
lion turtles.

620
00:48:00.713 --> 00:48:01.749
Whoa!

621
00:48:03.160 --> 00:48:04.846
It's beautiful.

622
00:48:06.966 --> 00:48:08.897
Long before my time.

623
00:48:08.897 --> 00:48:12.651
the lion turtles granted the
gift of bending to humans.

624
00:48:13.070 --> 00:48:15.578
These are their final resting grounds.

625
00:48:16.170 --> 00:48:19.318
This is where Sonum
came to learn their ways.

626
00:48:20.270 --> 00:48:23.438
I am certain that she left her staff here.

627
00:48:23.670 --> 00:48:24.970
Where should we start looking?

628
00:48:25.320 --> 00:48:27.970
Aang. you must connect with her.

629
00:48:29.145 --> 00:48:31.970
But no one can connect with Sonum.

630
00:48:32.170 --> 00:48:35.489
The spiritual power of the lion
turtles is still concentrated here.

631
00:48:36.020 --> 00:48:37.403
Let it guide you.

632
00:48:37.874 --> 00:48:39.195
We'll set out immediately.

633
00:48:39.220 --> 00:48:42.635
Actually. Taga.
we could really use your help here.

634
00:48:42.660 --> 00:48:45.663
If the denied are close behind.
we need to be ready.

635
00:48:45.688 --> 00:48:48.970
Yeah. and we're gonna need more
than Toph's metal bending to fix this.

636
00:48:49.420 --> 00:48:52.521
My bending got us through that storm.
What did you do?

637
00:48:52.546 --> 00:48:54.028
Steered with his feet.

638
00:48:54.053 --> 00:48:56.557
Repairs can wait. Aang needs me.

639
00:48:56.582 --> 00:49:00.433
Taga. please.
stay and help my friends.

640
00:49:01.120 --> 00:49:02.555
I'll be okay on my own.

641
00:49:03.259 --> 00:49:04.666
As you wish.

642
00:49:05.170 --> 00:49:08.153
We will begin repairs
for our voyage home.

643
00:49:09.566 --> 00:49:13.943
Everyone. I know I've asked
a lot of you on this journey.

644
00:49:13.968 --> 00:49:17.863
But we're about to accomplish
something that will change the world.

645
00:50:08.971 --> 00:50:10.545
"Let it guide you".

646
00:50:27.460 --> 00:50:28.460
Sonum?

647
00:50:46.620 --> 00:50:49.797
Oh. this is turning out
to be a nice little vacation.

648
00:50:50.564 --> 00:50:54.014
Aside from all the people trying
to kill us. and the tornadoes.

649
00:50:54.039 --> 00:50:56.565
Um. we're supposed 
to be fixing the ship?

650
00:50:56.590 --> 00:50:58.147
<i>You're doing great. buddy.</i>

651
00:50:58.440 --> 00:51:00.595
Has anyone seen Taga?

652
00:51:00.620 --> 00:51:03.593
Yes. we've all seen Taga.
He's so gorgeous.

653
00:51:03.630 --> 00:51:04.926
Geez. I get it.

654
00:51:05.613 --> 00:51:07.035
Oh. I see what you mean.

655
00:51:07.060 --> 00:51:08.692
He wandered off that way.

656
00:51:08.717 --> 00:51:11.142
No. maybe that way?

657
00:51:44.654 --> 00:51:45.457
Taga?

658
00:51:46.531 --> 00:51:47.992
Where are you going?

659
00:51:48.360 --> 00:51:50.126
Aang needs to be protected.

660
00:51:50.650 --> 00:51:51.650
I agree.

661
00:51:54.487 --> 00:51:57.162
I know my ways may seem unusual to you.

662
00:51:57.187 --> 00:52:01.877
But I assure you.
everything I do. I do for Aang.

663
00:52:01.902 --> 00:52:02.989
For Aang?

664
00:52:03.013 --> 00:52:04.277
Or for the staff?

665
00:52:05.775 --> 00:52:08.664
You have no idea all that we've lost.

666
00:52:08.689 --> 00:52:11.038
You've never known a world
 with airbenders.

667
00:52:11.648 --> 00:52:13.223
I know Aang.

668
00:52:13.720 --> 00:52:16.065
<i>He may be the last of his kind.</i>

669
00:52:16.090 --> 00:52:18.826
<i>But he's the reason this world knows peace.</i>

670
00:52:22.233 --> 00:52:26.794
<i>His values as an air nomad
have brought balance to chaos.</i>

671
00:52:28.471 --> 00:52:31.889
<i>It's because of Aang
that the Water Tribes.</i>

672
00:52:31.914 --> 00:52:35.258
<i>Earth Kingdom.
and Fire Nation now work together.</i>

673
00:52:35.283 --> 00:52:37.213
<i>Striving for harmony.</i>

674
00:52:37.611 --> 00:52:40.509
<i>A peace we once thought unattainable.</i>

675
00:52:42.565 --> 00:52:44.443
<i>You speak of peace.</i>

676
00:52:44.468 --> 00:52:47.238
There will never be
peace among the elements.

677
00:52:47.263 --> 00:52:48.617
<i>There never was.</i>

678
00:52:48.642 --> 00:52:52.078
<i>Your precious Republic City
 is built on lies.</i>

679
00:52:52.103 --> 00:52:54.190
<i>It's built on hope.</i>

680
00:52:54.415 --> 00:52:56.007
<i>Do you have hope. Taga?</i>

681
00:52:56.032 --> 00:52:59.020
Saving my people requires
more than just hope.

682
00:52:59.045 --> 00:53:00.995
It requires sacrifice.

683
00:53:01.020 --> 00:53:03.970
I saw you try to crush
the denied's airships.

684
00:53:04.045 --> 00:53:05.733
You were ready to kill them.

685
00:53:07.964 --> 00:53:10.771
<i>I know what kind
of airbender Aang is.</i>

686
00:53:12.976 --> 00:53:15.228
But what kind of airbender are you?

687
00:53:43.971 --> 00:53:45.724
Aang did well getting us here.

688
00:53:46.259 --> 00:53:50.266
There is great strength in him.
but weakness as well.

689
00:53:50.291 --> 00:53:51.478
Weakness?

690
00:53:51.592 --> 00:53:53.490
Yes. you.

691
00:54:10.284 --> 00:54:11.898
What the hog monkey?

692
00:54:15.291 --> 00:54:16.291
No!

693
00:54:35.170 --> 00:54:36.458
He trusted you.

694
00:54:43.717 --> 00:54:44.717
No.

695
00:56:05.055 --> 00:56:06.055
Brother.

696
00:56:09.211 --> 00:56:11.458
Taga. it's real.

697
00:56:15.971 --> 00:56:18.283
We can finally bring back airbending.

698
00:56:21.595 --> 00:56:22.989
Let's go tell the others.

699
00:56:23.071 --> 00:56:26.106
We can do this. me and you.

700
00:56:27.064 --> 00:56:29.025
I can't do this without my friends.

701
00:56:31.019 --> 00:56:34.445
Earth killed my people.
fire killed yours.

702
00:56:34.470 --> 00:56:38.345
The staff is the only way
 we can create a new air empire.

703
00:56:38.370 --> 00:56:40.970
One capable of defending itself.

704
00:56:40.995 --> 00:56:43.901
No. we can build a new future. Taga.

705
00:56:44.170 --> 00:56:46.212
But it has to be for everyone.

706
00:56:46.237 --> 00:56:48.460
The staff doesn't belong to everyone.

707
00:56:48.485 --> 00:56:49.970
It belongs to us.

708
00:56:49.971 --> 00:56:51.784
What have you done?

709
00:56:51.809 --> 00:56:55.329
As long as they were around.
you always put them ahead of our people.

710
00:56:55.835 --> 00:56:56.835
Don't you see?

711
00:56:56.860 --> 00:56:59.267
This is how we redeem ourselves.

712
00:56:59.814 --> 00:57:01.528
It doesn't matter that you ran then.

713
00:57:01.847 --> 00:57:03.810
As long as you stand with me now.

714
00:57:03.836 --> 00:57:04.211
No.

715
00:57:04.236 --> 00:57:05.917
Aang. listen to me.

716
00:57:05.942 --> 00:57:06.685
Katara.

717
00:57:06.710 --> 00:57:08.381
It's the only way.

718
00:57:08.406 --> 00:57:09.406
No.

719
00:57:22.048 --> 00:57:23.956
You're a traitor to your own.

720
00:57:24.074 --> 00:57:25.916
Just like Sonum.

721
00:58:03.778 --> 00:58:06.018
I wanted to do this
with you by my side.

722
00:58:07.425 --> 00:58:11.667
But if I must build a new air empire alone.
so be it.

723
00:58:20.657 --> 00:58:22.256
There's no way in.

724
00:58:22.529 --> 00:58:23.823
We have to turn back.

725
00:58:23.936 --> 00:58:26.589
No. we keep trying to push through.

726
00:58:38.958 --> 00:58:40.419
Sonum staff.

727
00:58:41.073 --> 00:58:42.893
Denied.

728
00:58:42.971 --> 00:58:44.970
The Avatar is dead.

729
00:58:45.413 --> 00:58:48.476
If you wish to build a new world 
where you have the power.

730
00:58:48.476 --> 00:58:50.156
I can give it to you.

731
00:59:05.242 --> 00:59:06.242
Appa.

732
00:59:06.618 --> 00:59:07.970
Katara.

733
00:59:08.525 --> 00:59:09.698
Katara.

734
00:59:11.278 --> 00:59:12.278
Katara.

735
00:59:13.220 --> 00:59:14.220
They're gone.

736
00:59:15.029 --> 00:59:16.109
It's all my fault.

737
00:59:17.220 --> 00:59:18.970
It's always been my fault.

738
00:59:19.620 --> 00:59:21.789
Ever since I ran away.

739
00:59:23.320 --> 00:59:28.783
No Avatar has ever fallen into such
shame as to join me here in my sorrow.

740
00:59:31.106 --> 00:59:32.970
Why do you grieve so. friend?

741
00:59:33.732 --> 00:59:35.012
Avatar Sonum?

742
00:59:38.270 --> 00:59:39.970
Taga murdered my friends.

743
00:59:40.520 --> 00:59:41.965
And now he has the staff.

744
00:59:42.128 --> 00:59:43.128
Taga.

745
00:59:43.153 --> 00:59:44.153
No.

746
00:59:44.200 --> 00:59:45.200
No. I...

747
00:59:45.225 --> 00:59:46.925
I stopped him.

748
00:59:47.120 --> 00:59:48.517
I hide the staff.

749
00:59:49.120 --> 00:59:50.882
What have you done?

750
00:59:51.802 --> 00:59:53.970
You're the one 
who gave him airbending.

751
00:59:54.519 --> 00:59:57.220
How could you give power
 to a monster?

752
00:59:57.520 --> 01:00:01.352
The Taga I gave bending
to was a different man.

753
01:00:02.773 --> 01:00:04.462
<i>It was a different time.</i>

754
01:00:05.187 --> 01:00:07.916
<i>The airbenders were the
peacekeepers of the four elements.</i>

755
01:00:08.620 --> 01:00:12.970
<i>We used our power to mediate
all conflict with nonviolence.</i>

756
01:00:13.163 --> 01:00:15.250
<i>But we were the fewest in numbers.</i>

757
01:00:16.263 --> 01:00:21.345
<i>For many years. we existed in a
beautiful balance of great prosperity.</i>

758
01:00:21.370 --> 01:00:23.524
<i>But the world began to shift.</i>

759
01:00:23.934 --> 01:00:26.344
<i>The earthbenders formed their own kingdom.</i>

760
01:00:26.368 --> 01:00:29.178
<i>separating from the other elemental tribes.</i>

761
01:00:29.656 --> 01:00:31.863
<i>The balance of the world was at risk.</i>

762
01:00:32.170 --> 01:00:34.437
<i>It was my duty to act.</i>

763
01:00:35.398 --> 01:00:40.195
<i>So I learned how to channel the energy of the
spirit world just as the lion turtles did.</i>

764
01:00:40.220 --> 01:00:43.031
<i>To give people the power of airbending.</i>

765
01:00:43.971 --> 01:00:48.970
<i>My most devout pupil. Taga.
was the first to receive it.</i>

766
01:00:49.470 --> 01:00:53.970
<i>I sent my new peacekeepers out
to help calm the growing unrest.</i>

767
01:00:54.620 --> 01:00:58.499
<i>But they were not prepared 
for the brutality of the new earth kingdom.</i>

768
01:01:00.971 --> 01:01:06.499
<i>Taga watched as his brothers
and sisters were all slaughtered.</i>

769
01:01:07.372 --> 01:01:10.437
<i>His heart darkened
by the violence of war.</i>

770
01:01:10.645 --> 01:01:15.221
<i>He now saw everyone 
who wasn't an air nomad as the enemy.</i>

771
01:01:16.118 --> 01:01:17.949
<i>Taga begged me to use the staff</i>

772
01:01:17.974 --> 01:01:21.126
<i>to create an army and to kill all
who would do us harm.</i>

773
01:01:21.596 --> 01:01:22.970
<i>I refused.</i>

774
01:01:23.497 --> 01:01:24.616
<i>So he stole it.</i>

775
01:01:25.888 --> 01:01:28.082
<i>When he connected
the staff to the temple.</i>

776
01:01:28.107 --> 01:01:31.538
<i>his energy was so corrupted 
by grief and rage</i>

777
01:01:31.563 --> 01:01:34.436
<i>that the power of the
spirit world consumed him.</i>

778
01:01:35.386 --> 01:01:40.946
<i>Taga became something more than human.
too powerful to kill.</i>

779
01:01:40.971 --> 01:01:43.981
<i>It took all my energy
to finally trap him</i>

780
01:01:44.006 --> 01:01:47.797
<i>high above the clouds
and no one would find him.</i>

781
01:01:48.457 --> 01:01:50.591
<i>I reclaimed the staff.</i>

782
01:01:50.615 --> 01:01:52.492
<i>but I was fatally wounded.</i>

783
01:01:53.220 --> 01:01:55.743
<i>Before the earth kingdom
could invade Jirana.</i>

784
01:01:55.768 --> 01:01:58.913
<i>I sent the remaining air nomads 
into the mountains.</i>

785
01:01:59.615 --> 01:02:04.117
<i>And I hid my temple in the spirit world
where no one could access its power.</i>

786
01:02:06.120 --> 01:02:08.274
<i>Then I locked the staff away</i>

787
01:02:08.298 --> 01:02:10.651
<i>where only the avatar could find it.</i>

788
01:02:11.998 --> 01:02:15.007
<i>I died hoping that one day </i>

789
01:02:15.007 --> 01:02:20.220
<i>another avatar would create more airbenders
and restore balance to this world.</i>

790
01:02:20.523 --> 01:02:23.345
<i>And that avatar is you. Aang.</i>

791
01:02:23.370 --> 01:02:27.395
You have to get my staff 
before Taga connects it to the temple.

792
01:02:27.420 --> 01:02:28.957
There's still time.

793
01:02:28.981 --> 01:02:31.404
Don't let my regret become yours.

794
01:02:31.770 --> 01:02:34.481
My friends and I fought hard 
for this peace.

795
01:02:34.820 --> 01:02:37.113
I won't let him start another war.

796
01:02:37.338 --> 01:02:39.262
Help me find a way back.

797
01:02:40.622 --> 01:02:41.970
Sonum?

798
01:02:42.944 --> 01:02:43.944
What's happening?

799
01:02:46.201 --> 01:02:48.484
No! No!

800
01:02:48.509 --> 01:02:50.642
Please! I have to fix this!

801
01:02:50.667 --> 01:02:52.826
This can't be it!
I can't die yet!

802
01:02:52.850 --> 01:02:55.406
Please! Not yet! No!

803
01:02:55.431 --> 01:02:56.678
- Aang?
- Katara?

804
01:02:56.703 --> 01:02:59.656
Come on. Aang! Come on!

805
01:02:59.680 --> 01:03:01.453
Aang! Move up!

806
01:03:02.023 --> 01:03:03.023
Aang!

807
01:03:04.626 --> 01:03:05.772
Katara.

808
01:03:05.796 --> 01:03:07.145
I was so worried.

809
01:03:07.596 --> 01:03:08.785
Aang.

810
01:03:08.809 --> 01:03:10.001
Sokka.

811
01:03:10.838 --> 01:03:12.395
I knew you'd pull through. buddy.

812
01:03:12.420 --> 01:03:13.303
Hey. Aang.

813
01:03:13.327 --> 01:03:14.241
Zuko.

814
01:03:14.665 --> 01:03:15.778
Momo.

815
01:03:16.499 --> 01:03:18.095
Welcome back. Twinkle Toes.

816
01:03:18.120 --> 01:03:20.055
Toph. you're okay.

817
01:03:21.516 --> 01:03:22.863
I thought you were all dead.

818
01:03:22.888 --> 01:03:26.221
We were. but Katara saved us.

819
01:03:26.420 --> 01:03:30.711
<i>The spiritual power of these waters
strengthened my healing abilities.</i>

820
01:03:33.059 --> 01:03:35.065
You're incredible. Katara.

821
01:03:36.758 --> 01:03:37.758
Where's Appa?

822
01:03:39.336 --> 01:03:40.970
Taga must have taken him.

823
01:03:41.608 --> 01:03:42.608
I'm sorry.

824
01:03:43.320 --> 01:03:44.320
No.

825
01:03:45.770 --> 01:03:47.577
I can't believe I trusted him.

826
01:03:49.551 --> 01:03:51.491
We'll get through this.

827
01:03:53.872 --> 01:03:55.895
<i>So. let me get this straight.</i>

828
01:03:55.920 --> 01:04:00.541
He's pulling Sonum's temple out of
the spirit world to gain unlimited power?

829
01:04:00.566 --> 01:04:03.760
And let me guess.
you want us to stop him?

830
01:04:03.970 --> 01:04:09.145
Sure. Only problem is your air bro
crushed our ship and stole your bison.

831
01:04:09.170 --> 01:04:12.543
Also. there's a massive
typhoon surrounding us!

832
01:04:15.696 --> 01:04:18.712
I don't say this very often.
but Sokka's right.

833
01:04:19.042 --> 01:04:21.145
- Thank you.
- Yep. we're stuck.

834
01:04:21.170 --> 01:04:24.511
And there aren't enough lion turtles
for all of us to have our own island.

835
01:04:24.536 --> 01:04:27.524
So. I'm calling this one.
I'm naming him Snappy.

836
01:04:27.549 --> 01:04:29.801
<i>Aw. Snappy is the best one.</i>

837
01:04:29.825 --> 01:04:30.881
<i>I know.</i>

838
01:04:31.170 --> 01:04:33.125
We may not know where Taga is.

839
01:04:33.614 --> 01:04:36.810
but we know what he's looking for
is in the spirit world.

840
01:04:37.301 --> 01:04:42.342
<i>And lucky for us. we're stuck in the most
spiritually charged place on the planet.</i>

841
01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:45.809
<i>So. I may be able to open
a portal to get us there.</i>

842
01:04:45.809 --> 01:04:48.308
<i>if I can summon an old friend.</i>

843
01:04:57.216 --> 01:04:58.481
Wow.

844
01:04:59.011 --> 01:05:00.518
The ocean spirit.

845
01:05:08.748 --> 01:05:11.450
This portal smells an awful 
lot like the fish market.

846
01:05:11.475 --> 01:05:13.095
I'm gonna go check on Snappy.

847
01:05:13.413 --> 01:05:14.983
Face your death with honor.

848
01:05:15.150 --> 01:05:16.150
I'm sorry.

849
01:05:16.510 --> 01:05:20.385
 I know I got us into this.
but I promise you I'll fix it.

850
01:05:20.712 --> 01:05:21.970
We'll fix it.

851
01:05:22.770 --> 01:05:23.770
Together.

852
01:05:27.167 --> 01:05:29.325
We're gonna die! We're gonna die!

853
01:05:39.976 --> 01:05:41.995
What? Where's my power pony?

854
01:05:42.020 --> 01:05:44.665
Were my hands always this small?

855
01:05:45.455 --> 01:05:47.601
It's baby Toph! Baby Toph!

856
01:05:49.220 --> 01:05:50.784
What the hog monkey?

857
01:05:51.510 --> 01:05:52.527
Old people.

858
01:05:52.581 --> 01:05:53.503
Grand.. Grand..?

859
01:05:53.528 --> 01:05:55.587
That's your sister. you weak head!

860
01:05:55.612 --> 01:05:58.156
Give me Toph.
There. there. Toph.

861
01:05:58.181 --> 01:05:59.604
Oh no. Zuko!

862
01:05:59.628 --> 01:06:01.700
What happened 
to your beautiful face?

863
01:06:01.725 --> 01:06:03.645
You look like a dried sea squid.

864
01:06:04.245 --> 01:06:05.245
No. Zuko!

865
01:06:06.019 --> 01:06:07.652
What's going on here?

866
01:06:09.129 --> 01:06:10.970
The spirit world is out of balance.

867
01:06:11.737 --> 01:06:12.970
And so are we.

868
01:06:15.444 --> 01:06:17.146
That's gotta be Taga.

869
01:06:38.963 --> 01:06:40.056
Oh no!

870
01:06:40.081 --> 01:06:42.552
He's pulling Sonum temple 
into our world!

871
01:06:42.577 --> 01:06:44.332
We're running out of time!

872
01:06:51.949 --> 01:06:53.369
Pretty good landing.

873
01:06:53.970 --> 01:06:57.190
Whoa! Humans! I love humans!

874
01:06:57.215 --> 01:07:00.100
Two brothers. their little sister.
and an elderly couple.

875
01:07:00.125 --> 01:07:00.742
- Couple!
- Couple!

876
01:07:00.767 --> 01:07:01.767
Not a couple!

877
01:07:01.792 --> 01:07:04.045
Whoa!
Looks like I touched a nerve.

878
01:07:04.070 --> 01:07:06.833
Oh. look at this one! Hello!

879
01:07:06.858 --> 01:07:09.318
Toph! No! Bad Toph!

880
01:07:09.471 --> 01:07:10.970
Don't bite strangers.

881
01:07:12.052 --> 01:07:15.946
Great spirit! Excuse me. did you
just come from that temple in the sky?

882
01:07:15.971 --> 01:07:17.408
I certainly did.

883
01:07:18.209 --> 01:07:19.704
It was my favorite hidey hole.

884
01:07:19.729 --> 01:07:23.289
Until that dark. yucky energy
started corrupting this whole place.

885
01:07:23.888 --> 01:07:26.859
Please. we need your help getting up there.

886
01:07:26.884 --> 01:07:28.883
It's my duty to stop this.

887
01:07:29.170 --> 01:07:30.720
I'm the Avatar.

888
01:07:31.457 --> 01:07:34.970
Ooh! The Avatar!

889
01:07:35.195 --> 01:07:36.727
Let me have a squiz at you.

890
01:07:36.752 --> 01:07:38.533
Okay. now with this eye.

891
01:07:38.937 --> 01:07:39.784
And this eye.

892
01:07:39.809 --> 01:07:41.735
Ooh. don't forget this eye.

893
01:07:41.937 --> 01:07:42.970
Can we hurry it up?

894
01:07:42.971 --> 01:07:43.970
I need to have a squiz.

895
01:07:43.971 --> 01:07:45.277
Sniff check!

896
01:07:47.775 --> 01:07:49.691
Ooh. that's Avatar material right there.

897
01:07:49.971 --> 01:07:52.431
Yes. it is. Oh!

898
01:07:52.456 --> 01:07:53.456
Yes. yes. yes. yes. yes!

899
01:07:53.481 --> 01:07:58.244
It appears the universe has brought
us together for a very important mission.

900
01:08:00.537 --> 01:08:01.970
To flee!

901
01:08:01.971 --> 01:08:03.970
And be alive!

902
01:08:03.971 --> 01:08:05.313
Wait! Come back!

903
01:08:05.338 --> 01:08:06.732
We're going the wrong way!

904
01:08:06.757 --> 01:08:07.756
Stop!

905
01:08:07.781 --> 01:08:10.353
Please. great spirit.
both of our worlds are in danger.

906
01:08:10.378 --> 01:08:11.662
No. no. no. no. no. no.

907
01:08:11.686 --> 01:08:13.377
I am not going back up there.

908
01:08:19.427 --> 01:08:22.614
Hmm. well. when you put it like that.
it does make more sense.

909
01:08:23.673 --> 01:08:27.682
Upon reflection. I've decided I shall
help you and your human-y friends.

910
01:08:27.707 --> 01:08:28.970
What did he say?

911
01:08:28.971 --> 01:08:30.181
Nice work. momo.

912
01:08:30.206 --> 01:08:31.868
Alright. in you go.

913
01:08:35.233 --> 01:08:38.689
By the way. no eating anything you find
in my teeth. as I'm saving that for later.

914
01:08:38.983 --> 01:08:40.970
Ready. set. get steady and rest.

915
01:08:40.971 --> 01:08:43.662
One and the two and
the you know what to do.

916
01:08:44.168 --> 01:08:45.168
Bluff!

917
01:08:50.698 --> 01:08:54.818
I know we haven't known each
other very long. but I love you!

918
01:08:54.925 --> 01:08:56.125
You don't have to say it back.

919
01:09:04.993 --> 01:09:06.866
Hey! You got your hair back!

920
01:09:06.891 --> 01:09:09.144
Why are my eyes cheery?
Was I crying?

921
01:09:10.458 --> 01:09:11.970
No way! Look!

922
01:09:12.345 --> 01:09:13.970
What? What is it?

923
01:09:13.971 --> 01:09:15.364
It's Republic City.

924
01:09:19.029 --> 01:09:21.970
We can't let him destroy
everything we've built.

925
01:09:22.210 --> 01:09:23.485
We won't.

926
01:09:38.778 --> 01:09:39.965
Boomerang!

927
01:09:57.463 --> 01:09:58.970
Give me the staff. Taga!

928
01:09:58.971 --> 01:10:01.402
I see I underestimated you. Avatar.

929
01:10:01.427 --> 01:10:03.970
Your friends are stronger than I thought.

930
01:10:04.397 --> 01:10:06.396
But you're too late.

931
01:10:14.223 --> 01:10:15.223
The Denied.

932
01:10:15.856 --> 01:10:18.252
You see. I did what you wanted. Aang.

933
01:10:18.740 --> 01:10:21.445
I returned airbending to the world.

934
01:10:23.163 --> 01:10:24.163
What's the plan?

935
01:10:24.245 --> 01:10:27.013
We'll deal with the Denied.
You have to get the staff.

936
01:10:27.570 --> 01:10:32.477
I will rebuild Geronimo and the ruins
of our enemies. just as they did on ours.

937
01:10:32.730 --> 01:10:35.242
A new air empire will rise.

938
01:10:35.808 --> 01:10:37.393
Kill them all.

939
01:10:55.614 --> 01:10:57.668
We have to get these people out of here.

940
01:11:02.144 --> 01:11:03.980
Whoa!

941
01:11:14.089 --> 01:11:15.642
Oh. yeah.

942
01:11:22.779 --> 01:11:25.366
Taga! Give it to me!

943
01:11:27.324 --> 01:11:28.630
This isn't the way.

944
01:11:28.630 --> 01:11:30.947
We can use the staff
 to bring back the balance.

945
01:11:31.074 --> 01:11:31.829
Peace!

946
01:11:31.854 --> 01:11:35.962
You care so much about your ideals 
that you'd let your people die!

947
01:11:36.659 --> 01:11:39.444
I will do anything 
to make sure they survive!

948
01:11:57.744 --> 01:11:59.556
My cabbages! My cabbages!

949
01:12:05.990 --> 01:12:07.334
My cabbages...!

950
01:12:07.874 --> 01:12:10.970
My cabbages!

951
01:12:24.012 --> 01:12:25.145
Don't do this.

952
01:12:25.212 --> 01:12:26.520
You have the power now.

953
01:12:26.545 --> 01:12:28.170
You can decide how to use it.

954
01:12:28.195 --> 01:12:29.454
I'm not like you.

955
01:12:29.478 --> 01:12:30.970
The world hasn't been good to me.

956
01:12:31.004 --> 01:12:32.920
The world is what we make it.

957
01:12:32.945 --> 01:12:34.618
Get away from her!

958
01:13:06.364 --> 01:13:07.842
Taga! Stop!

959
01:13:12.907 --> 01:13:15.335
You betrayed me!
You betrayed our culture!

960
01:13:15.360 --> 01:13:17.970
I gave you every chance
 to see the truth!

961
01:13:23.746 --> 01:13:26.355
Can you be in the Fire Nation?

962
01:13:27.996 --> 01:13:30.202
I'm fighting for the peace of all nations.

963
01:13:34.002 --> 01:13:37.761
Big talk from someone who sits
on a throne built on a century of war!

964
01:14:00.694 --> 01:14:04.443
I'm still the greatest
earthbender in the world!

965
01:14:28.170 --> 01:14:29.257
Oh no!

966
01:14:29.281 --> 01:14:30.686
I'm out of water!

967
01:14:33.359 --> 01:14:34.653
We got ya!

968
01:14:34.799 --> 01:14:37.922
And there's no Avatar here 
to save you.

969
01:14:39.066 --> 01:14:41.142
<i>Suck a cycle!</i>

970
01:14:44.829 --> 01:14:49.376
Let's see if your fancy new bending 
can beat some good ol' non-bending know-how!

971
01:14:56.229 --> 01:14:58.218
He comes away!

972
01:15:04.548 --> 01:15:06.355
You just got denied!

973
01:15:14.870 --> 01:15:15.797
Let's go!

974
01:15:15.822 --> 01:15:18.003
Good luck saving your city!

975
01:15:26.154 --> 01:15:28.720
We have to save as many people as we can!

976
01:15:46.835 --> 01:15:48.723
I know your pain.

977
01:15:48.747 --> 01:15:50.715
I know what you've been through.

978
01:15:51.372 --> 01:15:52.372
You don't know.

979
01:15:53.502 --> 01:15:57.769
I watched as all of my brothers
and sisters were slaughtered.

980
01:15:58.207 --> 01:16:01.682
And the Fire Nation burned
the Air Nomads to ash!

981
01:16:02.168 --> 01:16:03.343
Where were you?

982
01:16:04.097 --> 01:16:05.492
You ran!

983
01:16:26.277 --> 01:16:27.992
Taga!

984
01:16:37.688 --> 01:16:38.688
No!

985
01:17:01.101 --> 01:17:05.970
The full power of the Spirit World
 flows through me!

986
01:17:15.945 --> 01:17:18.975
This is what strength looks like!

987
01:18:12.058 --> 01:18:16.970
You should've run away like you
did all those years ago. little Avatar.

988
01:18:17.964 --> 01:18:19.148
I...

989
01:18:20.016 --> 01:18:21.019
won't...

990
01:18:21.043 --> 01:18:21.946
run.

991
01:18:21.971 --> 01:18:25.893
Then at least you'll die knowing
you're not the last Airbender!

992
01:19:03.013 --> 01:19:04.061
Aang...

993
01:19:12.398 --> 01:19:13.410
No!

994
01:20:20.626 --> 01:20:22.586
We could've been brothers!

995
01:20:23.034 --> 01:20:25.081
We could've done this together!

996
01:20:25.483 --> 01:20:27.193
It didn't have to end like this!

997
01:20:32.822 --> 01:20:34.397
It's Aang. He's got the staff!

998
01:20:34.422 --> 01:20:36.742
Yeah! Kick his butt. Mega Aang!

999
01:20:36.767 --> 01:20:38.489
No! Something's wrong!

1000
01:20:38.513 --> 01:20:40.145
The power is corrupting him!

1001
01:20:48.124 --> 01:20:49.391
No!

1002
01:20:58.574 --> 01:21:02.764
I dreamt of bringing the Air Nomads
back to the world as peacekeepers.

1003
01:21:02.789 --> 01:21:06.061
They could've been a beacon
of light for the world to follow.

1004
01:21:06.086 --> 01:21:07.638
But you ruined it!

1005
01:21:07.662 --> 01:21:10.248
You twisted my dream 
into a nightmare!

1006
01:21:10.654 --> 01:21:11.803
Finally.

1007
01:21:11.827 --> 01:21:14.339
You have the power
the Air Nomads need.

1008
01:21:14.646 --> 01:21:16.970
Maybe there is hope
 for you after all.

1009
01:21:27.548 --> 01:21:28.739
Do it!

1010
01:21:28.969 --> 01:21:30.174
Use the staff!

1011
01:21:30.422 --> 01:21:33.607
Show me you have the strength to bring
our people back!

1012
01:21:34.417 --> 01:21:35.417
Do it!

1013
01:22:12.170 --> 01:22:13.170
Aang...

1014
01:22:16.020 --> 01:22:19.281
You will do so many
great things as the Avatar.

1015
01:22:19.920 --> 01:22:23.514
But you must be prepared 
to do what frightens you the most.

1016
01:22:25.348 --> 01:22:29.970
Your people. your home.
we are always with you.

1017
01:22:46.603 --> 01:22:47.603
No!

1018
01:22:53.728 --> 01:22:54.728
No...

1019
01:23:18.331 --> 01:23:19.331
No!

1020
01:23:19.597 --> 01:23:20.890
My power!

1021
01:23:27.248 --> 01:23:29.558
No. No!

1022
01:23:39.370 --> 01:23:42.109
You fool! Why?

1023
01:23:42.648 --> 01:23:44.650
Why did you break it?

1024
01:23:45.177 --> 01:23:47.538
We could've fixed everything.

1025
01:23:48.731 --> 01:23:51.311
We can't erase the pain of the past.

1026
01:23:52.569 --> 01:23:53.889
We couldn't save them.

1027
01:23:54.049 --> 01:23:57.722
But it's our duty 
to protect our people.

1028
01:23:58.136 --> 01:24:01.639
Not at the cost of betraying
everything they stood for.

1029
01:24:01.664 --> 01:24:02.664
No.

1030
01:24:03.342 --> 01:24:04.669
It's time to let go.

1031
01:24:05.729 --> 01:24:07.569
You have to forgive yourself.

1032
01:24:10.270 --> 01:24:12.261
I have to forgive myself too.

1033
01:24:21.370 --> 01:24:24.299
Air Nomads are formed from the best.

1034
01:24:28.311 --> 01:24:32.359
We walk the world
for a moment in time.

1035
01:24:34.638 --> 01:24:38.970
Then we return 
to the eternal wind.

1036
01:24:54.821 --> 01:24:56.195
Aang!

1037
01:25:00.229 --> 01:25:01.329
Hey. Katara.

1038
01:25:01.870 --> 01:25:02.970
Hey. Aang.

1039
01:25:05.455 --> 01:25:06.455
Seriously?

1040
01:25:06.868 --> 01:25:08.970
You do realize you're falling. right?

1041
01:25:09.470 --> 01:25:11.676
Hey. if you ever get
tired of relying on Appa.

1042
01:25:11.701 --> 01:25:14.164
I can hook you up with
one of these babies.

1043
01:25:18.652 --> 01:25:20.970
I'll give you the best friend discount!

1044
01:25:35.070 --> 01:25:37.098
I don't know if
airbending will ever return.

1045
01:25:38.120 --> 01:25:40.970
But I know now that the
true power of the Air Nomads

1046
01:25:41.770 --> 01:25:42.970
was never their bending.

1047
01:25:43.520 --> 01:25:44.970
It was their values.

1048
01:25:45.670 --> 01:25:47.970
And that's a power
 I can pass on to others.

1049
01:25:49.270 --> 01:25:50.606
Avatar Aang.

1050
01:25:50.940 --> 01:25:54.383
you are the true embodiment 
of the Air Nomads.

1051
01:25:55.170 --> 01:25:58.492
Thank you for giving up
the power that I could not.

1052
01:25:59.345 --> 01:26:01.970
You give me hope
 for the future of our culture.

1053
01:26:15.911 --> 01:26:18.071
It's amazing. isn't it?

1054
01:26:18.520 --> 01:26:21.418
The first new air temple
 in centuries.

1055
01:26:22.698 --> 01:26:25.509
Republic City is finally complete.

1056
01:26:29.371 --> 01:26:32.747
A city for all nations.
just like you promised.

1057
01:26:33.720 --> 01:26:35.970
I never could have done
this without you. Katara.

1058
01:26:37.670 --> 01:26:40.357
Hey. everybody.
Sorry I kept you all waiting.

1059
01:26:40.670 --> 01:26:42.386
Are you ready for our big trip?

1060
01:26:43.827 --> 01:26:45.145
As my new acolytes.

1061
01:26:45.170 --> 01:26:49.263
you'll be helping me preserve
our culture for future generations.

1062
01:26:49.288 --> 01:26:54.026
So. who wants to search for artifacts
at an ancient abandoned temple?

1063
01:26:54.051 --> 01:26:55.051
Yay.

1064
01:26:55.076 --> 01:26:59.347
I'm only going to make sure you don't
try to release another beefy old airbender.

1065
01:26:59.372 --> 01:27:01.472
Yeah. I'm done with bad boys.

1066
01:27:13.618 --> 01:27:15.862
Avatar Sonum told me about this place.

1067
01:27:16.220 --> 01:27:19.970
so it's very possible that no one's
been here in hundreds of years.

1068
01:27:21.370 --> 01:27:24.266
Oh. is this an airbender relic?

1069
01:27:24.291 --> 01:27:25.815
I think that's just a rock.

1070
01:27:26.020 --> 01:27:27.970
But I love the enthusiasm.

1071
01:27:29.408 --> 01:27:30.408
Oh.

1072
01:27:33.804 --> 01:27:34.804
Keep your eyes open.

1073
01:27:35.156 --> 01:27:36.876
You never know 
what we might discover here.

1074
01:27:38.760 --> 01:27:39.760
Wouh.

1075
01:27:46.667 --> 01:27:48.433
I thought they were extinct.

1076
01:27:55.751 --> 01:27:57.411
I can't believe it.

1077
01:27:57.844 --> 01:27:59.636
The original airbenders.

1078
01:28:06.769 --> 01:28:09.102
Oh. can I have one?

1079
01:28:10.392 --> 01:28:12.390
Appa. yip-yip.

1080
01:28:14.859 --> 01:28:23.775
